radiographic_examinations.findings: Normal lung parenchyma and no pulmonary embolus.

Significant thickening of the bioprosthetic tricuspid valve leaflets with severely restricted leaflet motion and a large mass of low echo density. Confirmed a significant right-to-left interatrial shunt through a large patent foramen ovale (PFO).
Confirmed the interatrial shunt and demonstrated a significant tricuspid valve mass.
Findings suggested paradoxical embolism through the PFO.
